0:"";s:9:"wr_parent";s:3:"115";s:13:"wr_is_comment";s:1:"0";s:10:"wr_comment";s:1:"0";s:16:"wr_comment_reply";s:0:"";s:7:"ca_name";s:0:"";s:9:"wr_option";s:5:"html1";s:10:"wr_subject";s:33:"Defense Quality Management System";s:10:"wr_content";s:5268:"<div class="bo_wrap">
    <h3 class="title green">1. Defense Quality Management System</h3>
	<p class="marginBtm30">
		The Defense Quality Management System is a system managed and supported by the Defense Agency for Technology and Quality to enhance and ensure the quality of defense materials and improve the quality systems of defense industry companies.
	</p>
	<p class="marginBtm30">
		The South Korean military, in its efforts to ensure the quality assurance of its self-developed defense products, enhanced its specifications and adopted the ISO 9000:2000 standard introduced by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO) in 2000. Based on this standard, the military further strengthened the requirements to address the characteristics of the defense sector and ensure government rights protection, resulting in a comprehensive revision known as the Defense Quality Management System(DQMS) certification, referred to as KDS 05009000.
	</p>
	<p class="marginBtm50">
		As a result, defense companies have been able to enhance their quality management capabilities and improve reliability and efficiency in the defense sector.
	</p>
	
	<div class="img_box">
		<img class="dashed" src="/data/editor/2307/320292143001be21e456fdb9055fd97f_1689049102_8752.jpg" alt="Defense Quality Management System">
		<strong class="img_caption">&lt;&nbsp;Defense Quality Management System&nbsp;&gt;</strong>
	</div>
	
	<h3 class="title green">2. Defense Quality Management System Certification Procedure</h3>
	<ul class="list_box marginBtm50">
		<li class="positionR list26">
			<span class="positionA24">①</span><span class="fontB">System establishment</span> : Defense contractor or specialized research institutions seeking certification are required to establish a quality management system that complies with the Defense Quality Management System Standard (KDS 0050-90000)
		</li>
		<li class="positionR list26">
			<span class="positionA24">②</span><span class="fontB">System implementation</span> : After establishing a quality management system that complies with the Defense Quality Management System Standard (KDS 0050-90000), it must be implemented for a minimum of 6 months
		</li>
		<li class="positionR list26">
			<span class="positionA24">③</span><span class="fontB">Application review and corrective action</span> : Verification of the validity of the applied fields, items, and applicable standards, as well as the confirmation of the required documents, and supplementary measures if necessary
		</li>
		<li class="positionR list26">
			<span class="positionA24">④</span><span class="fontB">Certification Evaluation</span> : Conducting document and on-site assessments
		</li>
		<li class="positionR list26Last">
			<span class="positionA24">⑤</span><span class="fontB">Certification Acquisition</span> : Obtaining certification and awarding of the certificate based on the assessment results
		</li>
	</ul>
    
    <div class="img_box">
		<img class="dashed" src="/data/editor/2307/320292143001be21e456fdb9055fd97f_1689049149_0294.jpg" alt="KDS 0050-90000">
		<strong class="img_caption">&lt;&nbsp;KDS 0050-90000&nbsp;&gt;</strong>
	</div>
    
    <h3 class="title green">3. Effect of Defense Quality Management System Certification</h3>
	<ul class="list_box marginBtm50">
        <li class="positionR list14">
            <span class="positionA14">• &nbsp;</span>Extra points are awarded for bidding in government contracts.
        </li>
        <li class="positionR list14">
            <span class="positionA14">• &nbsp;</span>For contracts with the Defense Acquisition Program Administration, an additional score of 1.0 point is awarded to new entrant companies.
        </li>
        <li class="positionR list14">
            <span class="positionA14">• &nbsp;</span>An additional score of 0.5 points is awarded for contracts with the Public Procurement Service.
        </li>
        <li class="positionR list14">
            <span class="positionA14">• &nbsp;</span>Granting eligibility for participation in the Defense Quality Management Award → Granting additional score of 0.5 points for award.
        </li>
        <li class="positionR list14">
            <span class="positionA14">• &nbsp;</span>Perceiving the company as low risk during the establishment of government quality assurance activity plans, resulting in a reduction of the scope of activities.
        </li>
        <li class="positionR list14">
            <span class="positionA14">• &nbsp;</span>Increased profitability through the reduction of wasteful elements.
        </li>
        <li class="positionR list14">
            <span class="positionA14">• &nbsp;</span>Improved quality reliability through the reduction of product defect rates.
        </li>
        <li class="positionR list14">
            <span class="positionA14">• &nbsp;</span>Enhanced customer reliability through the reduction of customer complaints.
        </li>
        <li class="positionR list14Last">
            <span class="positionA14">• &nbsp;</span>Establishment of impeccable work standards, management criteria, and measurement criteria.
        </li>
    </ul>
    
